Rating: 3/5Fast but comes with temperature probelms

This review is from: Intel Core i7-7700K Kaby Lake Quad-Core 4.2 GHz LGA 1151 91W BX80677I77700K Desktop Processor

Pros: - Managed to OC to 5 ghz with 1.29 V.
- Extremely quick.

Cons: - There is a well known issue with this processor. It constantly has temperature spikes even without overclocking. For example, the processor will notify the motherboard that it is 30 degrees Celcius then suddenly jump to 77 C when you open a web browser and go back to 30 degrees one second after. This causes fans to spin very rapidly which is quite bothersome.
- Fan spin from temp spikes.

Other Thoughts: - If you don't care about fan noise, then this is an excellent product.
- Buy quiet CPU cooler fans and case fans.
- You've been warned.
- Also, no my temp spikes Aren't from OC or thermal paste or whatever other reason you may bring up as an excuse to buy this processor.
- Some managed the fan noise with certain fan curves, however, never completely eliminated it.

Rating: 5/5Large temp spikes, but not a problem even with a budget cooler.

This review is from: Intel Core i7-7700K Kaby Lake Quad-Core 4.2 GHz LGA 1151 91W BX80677I77700K Desktop Processor

Pros: As others have said, it's very fast. I'm playing Fallout 4 max settings with a GTX 1060 and this cpu is not even sweating.

Cons: Not really a con but I'm seeing large temp spikes when opening apps etc. I'm sitting idle around 30c and when I open Firefox I'm seeing 60-65c for a few seconds right before cooling back down to 30c.

Other Thoughts: I'm using a coolermaster hyper 212 evo to cool. I have not seen temps above 80c. The highest I saw was during 3d mark timespy cpu test. During normal gaming, I peak at 70c. I'm not overclocking the cpu right now but my memory is overclocked to 3000.

Since these temp spikes are large, the standard cpu fan curve that comes with your motherboard is not going to like it. By default my fan curve was set to run the cpu fan 100% at 70c. I'm hitting this temp often during gaming and multitasking. I would be sitting in low 30s and all of sudden spike, and my cpu fan would go to 100% which is super loud before quieting down again in a few seconds which was very annoying. I changed the curve to engage to 100% at 80c which is still 20c below the TJ. max. I don't really hear the fan freak out anymore when gaming or browsing which use to happen a lot.

It is super important you install the cpu cooler correctly as this cpu runs hot. If you are planning on overclocking this cpu, make sure you don't use a budget cpu cooler, and have good case airflow.

Cons: A proper watercooling setup is necessary for any sort of overclocking. This isn't necessarily a con for me as I already own sufficient cooling. (H110i GTX)

Other Thoughts: Stop trying to push 5GHz on air coolers and you wont get over 80+celcius!

    How many pci lanes does Kaby Lake processors support, 28 or 40?
    Thomas L on Feb 12, 2017
    BEST ANSWER: As I understand it, the Kaby Lake processor supports 16 dedicated PCI-E 3.0 lanes for the PCI Express slots. The chipset on the motherboard has additional lanes so with a Z270 chipset you get an additional 24 lanes for peripherals for a total of 40 lanes total. If your motherboard has a H270 or a Z170 chipset then you only have 20 additional lanes for a total of 36.

    Condition Guidelines

    The following guidelines apply to all product categories unless otherwise indicated within specific categories.

    • New : This means the product will ship as received by the manufacturer, sealed, with all advertised components, and with the manufacturer warranty.
    • Refurbished : This means the product was tested and repaired as required to meet the standards of the refurbisher, which may or may not be the original manufacturer. Any exceptions to the condition of the item outside the manufacturerâs information should be provided in the listing, up to and including warranty details.
    • Open Box : Newegg only guarantees your receipt of the Open Box product with the purchase of this item. Any accessories MAY OR MAY NOT be included. Newegg will NOT send you any missing accessories, even if it is required to use all of the itemâs functions.Open Box items usually do not come with manufacturer or vendor warranty or technical support. However, warranty support may be available if an item was never registered by a previous owner. Please contact the manufacturer to check.
    • Used - Like New : This means that the product has been opened, possibly used but is in perfect condition with no signs of cosmetic or functional defect. Product includes warranty, and accessories found with the original product. Product may or may not be in the original packaging. Returned items with minor packaging defects fall under this category.
    • Used - Very Good : This means that the product has been opened, may show slight signs of use and cosmetic blemish, and may be missing minor accessories, but remain in excellent condition. Product does not come with warranty unless stated otherwise in product description.
    • Used - Good : This means that the product has been used, may show clear signs of use and may be missing minor accessories, but remain in good condition. Product does not come with warranty unless stated otherwise in product description.
    • Used - Acceptable : This means that the product shows clear signs of use, cosmetic defect, and may be missing minor accessories and manual, but remain in working condition. Product does not come with warranty unless stated otherwise in product description. Functionality issues beyond signs of use should be disclosed in product description.
